(129, 1, '2016-02-29 08:17:48', '2016-02-29 08:17:48', 'Freeform Portland is a 501(3)c nonprofit organization benefiting our community through providing a number of public resources:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Broadcasting Musicology classes</li>\r\n	<li>Music library</li>\r\n	<li>Promoting local music and arts events</li>\r\n	<li>More!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nOur station runs on volunteer and financial support from our friends and neighbors and we are grateful for any and all contributions.\r\n\r\nYour donation to Freeform Portland can be tax-deductible! Email donate@freeformportland.org\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Feel free to send a check, if  you''d like. Please make checks out to Freeform Portland and mail to:\r\nFreeform Portland\r\n801 N. Killingsworth St.\r\nPortland OR 97217</p>\r\nFreeform Portland will gratefully accept your donation of records, CDs and headphones in good working condition, plus office supplies, snacks, and more — please email donate@freeformportland.org to get in touch with a donations volunteer. You can also keep an eye out for the donation jar at most KFFP events.\r\n\r\nThanks so much!', 'Donate', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '32-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-29 08:17:48', '2016-02-29 08:17:48', '', 32, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/32-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(57, 3, '2016-02-17 04:49:41', '2016-02-17 04:49:41', '<h2>Become a Freeform Portland Volunteer!</h2>\r\nFreeform Portland, KFFP-LP 90.30 FM, is a nonprofit, volunteer-run community radio station providing a number of public resources. Interested in becoming a Freeform Portland volunteer? Our volunteers gain job skills, learn about music, and meet new people all while giving back to their communities. It’s a great opportunity for people with a little bit of free time and a lot to gain. Our volunteer committees power the station in the following ways:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Broadcasting Operations</li>\r\n	<li>Grant Writing</li>\r\n	<li>Fundraising/Events</li>\r\n	<li>Marketing</li>\r\n	<li>Music Library</li>\r\n	<li>Volunteer</li>\r\n	<li>Website</li>\r\n	<li>Zine</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nRead more about each committee below, and fill out our <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeMMp97qi8aU429o-u_zS51cR15UrYUI7bIXFb5t9ZtLr7g6g/viewform?c=0&amp;w=1" target="_blank">KFFP Volunteer Contact Form</a> to be contacted by a member of our Volunteer Committee.\r\n<h3>Broadcasting Operations</h3>\r\nResponsibilities include maintaining the station''s transmitter, turntables, microphones, wiring, and everything else that counts as broadcasting equipment. Members also collect and organize supplies for KFFP office operations.\r\n<h3>Grant Writing</h3>\r\nGrant writers obtain the vast majority of Freeform Portland''s financial support by soliciting grants from donor organizations. Good letter-writers should apply!\r\n<h3>Fundraising/Events</h3>\r\nThis group plans and puts on shows, parties, DJ nights, and other events that help bring much-needed funds to KFFP. Members also help develop and distribute merch like t-shirts, pins, koozies, and more.\r\n<h3>Marketing</h3>\r\nHelp raise community awareness of our station to bring in new listeners.\r\n<h3>Music Library</h3>\r\nThis group keeps the music library stocked, organized, and in good working condition. Music Library Committee volunteers send music requests to record labels and tag new additions to help the KFFP community find what we''re looking for.\r\n<h3>Volunteer</h3>\r\nWe always need new volunteers! This committee finds fresh meat and places people where they can be the most comfortable and effective at helping us out.\r\n<h3>Website</h3>\r\nVolunteers with website development skills (coding, project planning, etc.) should consider joining this committee. This is the crew that designs the site, writes the content, and develops the features like our streaming music player.\r\n<h3>Zine</h3>\r\nThe Zine Committee solicits and creates art and copy, for our lovely Freeform Portland zine, and then publishes and distributes it four times per year for 25 cents an issue.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Volunteering with us is a requirement for all of our on-air DJs. Don’t want to be on the air? No problem! Not everyone does, and we can still use your help. To learn more about volunteering with us, fill out the <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/118lWyMgnMCVz3_xNOwMkUqXjYDnjq3wJPpVorB3BaBk/viewform?c=0&amp;w=1">KFFP Volunteer Contact Form</a> or email </span><a href="mailto:volunteer@freeformportland.org"><span style="font-weight: 400;">volunteer@freeformportland.org</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Freeform Portland also accepts </span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="http://www.freeformportland.org/donate/" target="_blank">donations</a></span><span style="font-weight: 400;">!</span>', 'Volunteer', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'volunteer', '', '', '2016-08-31 20:12:03', '2016-08-31 20:12:03', '', 13, 'http://beta.freeformportland.org/?page_id=57', 1, 'page', '', 0),
(58, 3, '2016-02-17 04:11:03', '2016-02-17 04:11:03', '<h2>Volunteering with Freeform Portland is fun!</h2>\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Freeform Portland is a nonprofit, volunteer-run radio station providing a free resource to our neighbors thanks to the generous help of our community members. </span>\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Our volunteer committees help the station in the following ways:</span>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><b>Grant Writing:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Researching and soliciting grants from sustaining institutions</span></li>\r\n	<li><b>Marketing/Fundraising/Events: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Planning DJ nights, developing and selling merch</span></li>\r\n	<li><b>Music Library: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Maintaining our music library, soliciting CDs/records, and labeling new arrivals</span></li>\r\n	<li><b>Broadcasting Operations / Studio: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Setting up the station and making necessary updates and repairs. Locating furniture, decorations, and supplies</span></li>\r\n	<li><b>Volunteer: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Soliciting and coordinating new staff</span></li>\r\n	<li><b>Website:</b><span style="font-weight: 400;"> Designing, coding, and copywriting</span></li>\r\n	<li><b>Zine: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">Collecting and writing content, pasting up, printing, and delivering</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFreeform Portland volunteers gain job skills, learn about music, and meet new people all while giving back to their communities. It’s a great way to TKTKTKTK.\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Volunteering with us is a requirement for all of our on-air DJs. Don’t want to be on the air? No problem! We can still use your help. To learn more about volunteering with us, email </span><a href="mailto:volunteer@freeformportland.org"><span style="font-weight: 400;">volunteer@freeformportland.org</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Freeform Portland also accepts </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">donations</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">!</span>', 'Volunteer', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '57-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-17 04:11:03', '2016-02-17 04:11:03', '', 57, 'http://beta.freeformportland.org/blog/57-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
