(70, 2, '2016-02-17 05:05:54', '2016-02-17 05:05:54', '<h1>Freeform Portland</h1>\r\nFreeform Portland (KFFP 90.3 FM) is a nonprofit, independent community radio station whose purpose is fostering independent, local, experimental, and underground music, alongside arts and public affairs programming that reflect our community. Freeform Portland is radio for the people, by the people.', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '13-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-17 05:05:54', '2016-02-17 05:05:54', '', 13, 'http://beta.freeformportland.org/blog/13-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(67, 2, '2016-02-17 04:52:45', '2016-02-17 04:52:45', '<h1>Freeform Portland</h1>\r\nWouldn''t it be great to have a fun radio station in Portland that plays a variety of great music morning, noon and night with no commercials? In 2015, three companies own over 75% of Portland''s radio dial. We want you to join our team of media rebels. Help us further liberate local airwaves from commercial control. Just like you can''t have too many local coffee shops or startup restaurants, you can not have too many local commercial-free radio stations.', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '13-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-17 04:52:45', '2016-02-17 04:52:45', '', 13, 'http://beta.freeformportland.org/blog/13-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(71, 2, '2016-10-24 17:53:05', '2016-10-24 17:53:05', '<img class="alignnone wp-image-1047 size-full" src="http://www.freeformportland.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Zach-Stricker-KFFP-Image.jpg" alt="KFFP Image by Zach Stricker" width="939" height="939" />\n<h1>Liberate the Local Airwaves</h1>\nFreeform Portland KFFP-LP 90.3 FM is run by a dedicated group of music enthusiasts and DJs from Portland, Oregon. We''re local volunteers who want to reclaim some portion of our airwaves from corporate control.\n\nWe offer:\n<ul>\n	<li>Public broadcasting classes and music education opportunities</li>\n	<li>DJs with unique cultural perspectives and fresh voices from the local community</li>\n	<li>Exposure to local and touring musicians</li>\n	<li>Experimental music and arts programming, under-represented in Portland</li>\n</ul>\nLet''s uphold community radio and freeform programming that truly reflects and celebrates our local communities.\n\n<a href="http://www.freeformportland.org/donate" target="_blank">Donate to KFFP!</a>\n\nCan''t donate? Help out!\n\n&nbsp;', '', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '5-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-10-24 17:53:05', '2016-10-24 17:53:05', '', 5, 'http://beta.freeformportland.org/blog/5-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(69, 3, '2016-03-25 04:35:29', '2016-03-25 04:35:29', '<h2>Become a Freeform Portland Volunteer!</h2>\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Freeform Portland is a nonprofit, volunteer-run community radio station providing a number of public resources. Interested in becoming a Freeform Portland volunteer? Our staff gains job skills, learns about music, and meets new people all while giving back to their communities. It’s a great opportunity for people with a little bit of free time and a lot to gain. </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Our volunteer committees power the station in the following ways:</span>\n<ul>\n	<li>Broadcasting Operations / Studio</li>\n	<li>Grant Writing</li>\n	<li>Fundraising/Events</li>\n	<li>Marketing</li>\n	<li>Music Library</li>\n	<li>Volunteer</li>\n	<li>Website</li>\n	<li>Zine</li>\n</ul>\nRead more about each committee below, and fill out our <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/118lWyMgnMCVz3_xNOwMkUqXjYDnjq3wJPpVorB3BaBk/viewform?c=0&amp;w=1">KFFP Volunteer Contact Form</a> to be contacted by a member of our Volunteer Committee.\n<h3>Broadcasting Operations / Studio</h3>\nResponsibilities include maintaining the station''s transmitter, turntables, microphones, wiring, and everything else that counts as broadcasting equipment. Members also collect and organize supplies for KFFP office operations.\n<h3>Grant Writing</h3>\nGrant writers obtain the vast majority of Freeform Portland''s financial support by soliciting grants from donor organizations. Good letter-writers should apply!\n<h3>Fundraising/Events</h3>\nThis group plans and puts on shows, parties, DJ nights, and other events that help bring much-needed funds to KFFP. Members also help develop and distribute merch like t-shirts, pins, koozies, and more.\n<h3>Marketing</h3>\nThe Marketing Committee raises community awareness of our station to bring in new listeners. Formerly a part of the Fundraising/Events committee.\n<h3>Music Library</h3>\nThis group keeps the music library stocked, organized, and in good working condition. Music Library Committee volunteers send music requests to record labels and tag new additions to help the KFFP community find what we''re looking for.\n<h3>Volunteer</h3>\nWe always need new volunteers! This committee finds fresh meat and places people where they can be the most comfortable and effective at helping us out.\n<h3>Website</h3>\nVolunteers with website development skills (coding, project planning, etc.) should consider joining this committee. This is the crew that designs the site, writes the content, and develops the features like our streaming music player.\n<h3>Zine</h3>\nThe Zine Committee solicits and creates art and copy, for our lovely Freeform Portland zine, and then publishes and distributes it four times per year for 25 cents an issue.\n\n<hr />\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Volunteering with us is a requirement for all of our on-air DJs. Don’t want to be on the air? No problem! Not everyone does, and we can still use your help. To learn more about volunteering with us, fill out the <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/118lWyMgnMCVz3_xNOwMkUqXjYDnjq3wJPpVorB3BaBk/viewform?c=0&amp;w=1">KFFP Volunteer Contact Form</a> or email </span><a href="mailto:volunteer@freeformportland.org"><span style="font-weight: 400;">volunteer@freeformportland.org</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Freeform Portland also accepts </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">donations</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">!</span>', 'Volunteer', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '57-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-03-25 04:35:29', '2016-03-25 04:35:29', '', 57, 'http://beta.freeformportland.org/blog/57-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(676, 2, '2016-08-08 23:12:18', '2016-08-08 23:12:18', '<h2>Become a Freeform Portland Volunteer!</h2>\r\n<blockquote>We’re NOW accepting DJ show applications for our October 2016 to March 2017 schedule! Fill out a Weekly Show Request Form <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeaBCShJgFkNCzL5NUeGP7RfOgYHZr3RKKtcItMsLI7qfGmyA/viewform" target="_blank">here</a>. The deadline for submissions is August 20, 2016.</blockquote>\r\nFreeform Portland, KFFP-LP 90.30 FM, is a nonprofit, volunteer-run community radio station providing a number of public resources. Interested in becoming a Freeform Portland volunteer? Our volunteers gain job skills, learn about music, and meet new people all while giving back to their communities. It’s a great opportunity for people with a little bit of free time and a lot to gain. Our volunteer committees power the station in the following ways:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Broadcasting Operations</li>\r\n	<li>Grant Writing</li>\r\n	<li>Fundraising/Events</li>\r\n	<li>Marketing</li>\r\n	<li>Music Library</li>\r\n	<li>Volunteer</li>\r\n	<li>Website</li>\r\n	<li>Zine</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nRead more about each committee below, and fill out our <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeMMp97qi8aU429o-u_zS51cR15UrYUI7bIXFb5t9ZtLr7g6g/viewform?c=0&amp;w=1" target="_blank">KFFP Volunteer Contact Form</a> to be contacted by a member of our Volunteer Committee.\r\n<h3>Broadcasting Operations</h3>\r\nResponsibilities include maintaining the station''s transmitter, turntables, microphones, wiring, and everything else that counts as broadcasting equipment. Members also collect and organize supplies for KFFP office operations.\r\n<h3>Grant Writing</h3>\r\nGrant writers obtain the vast majority of Freeform Portland''s financial support by soliciting grants from donor organizations. Good letter-writers should apply!\r\n<h3>Fundraising/Events</h3>\r\nThis group plans and puts on shows, parties, DJ nights, and other events that help bring much-needed funds to KFFP. Members also help develop and distribute merch like t-shirts, pins, koozies, and more.\r\n<h3>Marketing</h3>\r\nHelp raise community awareness of our station to bring in new listeners.\r\n<h3>Music Library</h3>\r\nThis group keeps the music library stocked, organized, and in good working condition. Music Library Committee volunteers send music requests to record labels and tag new additions to help the KFFP community find what we''re looking for.\r\n<h3>Volunteer</h3>\r\nWe always need new volunteers! This committee finds fresh meat and places people where they can be the most comfortable and effective at helping us out.\r\n<h3>Website</h3>\r\nVolunteers with website development skills (coding, project planning, etc.) should consider joining this committee. This is the crew that designs the site, writes the content, and develops the features like our streaming music player.\r\n<h3>Zine</h3>\r\nThe Zine Committee solicits and creates art and copy, for our lovely Freeform Portland zine, and then publishes and distributes it four times per year for 25 cents an issue.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Volunteering with us is a requirement for all of our on-air DJs. Don’t want to be on the air? No problem! Not everyone does, and we can still use your help. To learn more about volunteering with us, fill out the <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/118lWyMgnMCVz3_xNOwMkUqXjYDnjq3wJPpVorB3BaBk/viewform?c=0&amp;w=1">KFFP Volunteer Contact Form</a> or email </span><a href="mailto:volunteer@freeformportland.org"><span style="font-weight: 400;">volunteer@freeformportland.org</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Freeform Portland also accepts </span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="https://www.paypal.com/us/cgi-bin/webscr?cmd=_flow&amp;SESSION=ETpls-fsawDeCSuaqZUJ9xRsBJVuAUQhJiLLyhXaPLzfhDlAsLdSSr9pGLO&amp;dispatch=5885d80a13c0db1f8e263663d3faee8de2b8031b89187c030b37e57608011f58" target="_blank">donations</a></span><span style="font-weight: 400;">!</span>', 'Volunteer', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '57-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-08 23:12:18', '2016-08-08 23:12:18', '', 57, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/57-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(132, 1, '2016-03-06 00:52:52', '2016-03-06 00:52:52', 'Freeform Portland is a 501(3)c nonprofit organization benefiting our community through providing a number of public resources:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Broadcasting Musicology classes</li>\r\n	<li>Music library</li>\r\n	<li>Promoting local music and arts events</li>\r\n	<li>More!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nOur station runs on volunteer and financial support from our friends and neighbors and we are grateful for any and all contributions.\r\n\r\nYour donation to Freeform Portland can be tax-deductible!\r\n\r\n<form action="https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr" method="post" target="_top">\r\n<input type="hidden" name="cmd" value="_s-xclick">\r\n<input type="hidden" name="hosted_button_id" value="EXDPWNQFGWYEL">\r\n<input type="image" src="https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/btn/btn_donateCC_LG.gif" border="0" name="submit" alt="PayPal - The safer, easier way to pay online!">\r\n<img alt="" border="0" src="https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/scr/pixel.gif" width="1" height="1">\r\n</form>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Feel free to send a check, if  you''d like. Please make checks out to Freeform Portland and mail to:\r\nFreeform Portland\r\n801 N. Killingsworth St.\r\nPortland OR 97217</p>\r\nFreeform Portland will gratefully accept your donation of records, CDs and headphones in good working condition, plus office supplies, snacks, and more — please email donate@freeformportland.org to get in touch with a donations volunteer. You can also keep an eye out for the donation jar at most KFFP events.\r\n\r\nThanks so much!', 'Donate', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '32-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-06 00:52:52', '2016-03-06 00:52:52', '', 32, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/32-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
