(128, 1, '2016-03-09 21:09:12', '2016-03-09 21:09:12', 'Freeform Portland is a 501(3)c nonprofit organization benefiting our community through providing a number of public resources:\n<ul>\n	<li>Broadcasting Musicology classes</li>\n	<li>Music library</li>\n	<li>Promoting local music and arts events</li>\n	<li>More!</li>\n</ul>\nOur station runs on volunteer and financial support from our friends and neighbors and we are grateful for any and all contributions.\n\nYour donation to Freeform Portland can be tax-deductible!\n\n<form action="https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr" method="post" target="_top">\n<input type="hidden" name="cmd" value="_s-xclick">\n<input type="hidden" name="hosted_button_id" value="EXDPWNQFGWYEL">\n<input type="image" src="https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/btn/btn_donate_LG.gif" border="0" name="submit" alt="Donate to KFFP">\n</form>\n\n<p style="text-align: left;">Feel free to send a check, if  you''d like. Please make checks out to Freeform Portland and mail to:\nFreeform Portland\n801 N. Killingsworth St.\nPortland OR 97217</p>\nFreeform Portland will gratefully accept your donation of records, CDs and headphones in good working condition, plus office supplies, snacks, and more — please email donate@freeformportland.org to get in touch with a donations volunteer. You can also keep an eye out for the donation jar at most KFFP events.\n\nThanks so much!', 'Donate', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '32-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-03-09 21:09:12', '2016-03-09 21:09:12', '', 32, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/32-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(130, 1, '2016-02-29 08:18:38', '2016-02-29 08:18:38', '<h3>How can I donate? Are donations tax deductible?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Donations are 501(c)3 tax-deductible. Get a limted edition shirt through our <a href="http://bit.ly/1Hvk1qA">indiegogo</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Why does Portland need another listener-supported radio station?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>3 companies own 75% of our local airwaves. We feel that we have to do something about that. We are working in cooperation with every non-commercial radio station in Portland. Seriously. It''s a team effort. The only way to make radio better in Portland is to keep making better radio in Portland.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>What''s the Frequency, Kenneth? Projected launch date? Where''s the studio?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>With your help we will test FM broadcasting in 2015 and launch in 2016. Please sign up for the email list on this page.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Can I have a show? Will you play my band''s album please?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>More info soon! Please sign up for the email list on this page</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Volunteer opportunities? How can I help?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>email volunteer@freeformportland.org and tell us about yourself.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Will there be commercials? I''ll be able to hear this station from my house /car?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Freeform Portland is a non-profit commercial-free radio station coming to Low-Power FM in Portland in 2016. We''re using the same engineering team that created KZME and XRAY and working alongside every non-commercial radio station in Portland. We''re stoked to get to broadcasting ASAP and we need your help.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-29 08:18:38', '2016-02-29 08:18:38', '', 16, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/16-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(131, 1, '2016-02-29 08:18:46', '2016-02-29 08:18:46', '<h3>How can I donate? Are donations tax deductible?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Donations are 501(c)3 tax-deductible. Get a limited edition shirt through our <a href="http://bit.ly/1Hvk1qA">indiegogo</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Why does Portland need another listener-supported radio station?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>3 companies own 75% of our local airwaves. We feel that we have to do something about that. We are working in cooperation with every non-commercial radio station in Portland. Seriously. It''s a team effort. The only way to make radio better in Portland is to keep making better radio in Portland.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>What''s the Frequency, Kenneth? Projected launch date? Where''s the studio?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>With your help we will test FM broadcasting in 2015 and launch in 2016. Please sign up for the email list on this page.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Can I have a show? Will you play my band''s album please?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>More info soon! Please sign up for the email list on this page</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Volunteer opportunities? How can I help?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>email volunteer@freeformportland.org and tell us about yourself.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Will there be commercials? I''ll be able to hear this station from my house /car?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Freeform Portland is a non-profit commercial-free radio station coming to Low-Power FM in Portland in 2016. We''re using the same engineering team that created KZME and XRAY and working alongside every non-commercial radio station in Portland. We''re stoked to get to broadcasting ASAP and we need your help.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-02-29 08:18:46', '2016-02-29 08:18:46', '', 16, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/16-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
