(143, 1, '2016-03-11 19:38:39', '2016-03-11 19:38:39', '', 'thought-crime', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', 'thought-crime', '', '', '2016-03-11 19:38:39', '2016-03-11 19:38:39', '', 13, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/thought-crime.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
(144, 1, '2016-03-11 19:38:52', '2016-03-11 19:38:52', '<img src="http://www.freeformportland.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/thought-crime.jpg" alt="thought-crime" width="700" height="655" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-143" />\r\n\r\n<h1>About Freeform Portland</h1>\r\nFreeform Portland is a nonprofit, independent, community-driven radio station broadcasting at KFFP 90.3 FM. Our purpose is to foster independent, local, experimental, and underground music alongside arts and public affairs programming that authentically reflects our communities.\r\n<h1>Community-Driven</h1>\r\nWe need more community radio. For a city with a metro area of over two million creative people, Portland has a surprisingly small amount of non-commercial, independent radio stations on the air. The vast majority of radio stations broadcasting in our city are controlled by ClearChannel/iHeartMedia. Community radio provides an invaluable venue for more voices to be heard and more perspectives to be represented in public media. We love local stations like KBOO, KMHD, and XRAY. Freeform Portland is proud to join them in taking back the airwaves from corporate control.\r\n<h1>Freeform Radio</h1>\r\nWhat is freeform radio? Freeform radio is a programming format in which the DJ is given total control over what to play, regardless of music genre or commercial interests. Freeform radio stands in contrast to most commercial radio stations where DJs have little or no influence over programming structure or playlists. Ken Freedman from WFMU (the longest running freeform radio station in the United States) explains the importance of freeform radio and what Freeform Portland is up to <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z-qEUkYWnck" target="_blank">here</a>.\r\n<h1></h1>', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '13-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-11 19:38:52', '2016-03-11 19:38:52', '', 13, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/13-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(607, 23, '2016-06-28 05:44:15', '2016-06-28 05:44:15', 'am a Pacific Northwest hiphop underground artist, and as an underground artist i wanna provide a service to a vast rise in the music scene in the Portland and Vancouver area, not only here but all over the world. My goal is to host a radio show where artist have the ability no matter what to get there music played on the radio for everyone to hear because that was there original intentions anyways, every artist wants to be heard. Now a days it can be so difficult to get the right opportunity or connections to get that feature on a radio station. Here on my station each show will have a set playlist for the night all full of unknown, up and coming, independent and local artist as well as classics everyone enjoys. Not only that but the show will feature discussion topics interviews with artist, contest and more.', 'Crooked Car Tunes', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '184-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-06-28 05:44:15', '2016-06-28 05:44:15', '', 184, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/184-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(608, 23, '2016-06-28 05:57:24', '2016-06-28 05:57:24', 'Kitty McKlaine''s Dance Party: A mix of current through 80s new wave, synth pop, electro and dance music.\n\nIn Crates We Dig: An exploration of music recorded on vinyl across many eras and genres. Each hour of the show will focus on a particular genre but the variety from hour to hour will be wide and unpredictable.', 'Kitty McKlaine''s Dance Party / In Crates We Dig (Alternating)', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '195-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-06-28 05:57:24', '2016-06-28 05:57:24', '', 195, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/195-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
