(619, 2, '2016-07-15 22:11:41', '2016-07-15 22:11:41', '<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-580" src="http://www.freeformportland.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Record-Player-II_Nick-Pennell.jpg" alt="Freeform Portland Vinyl DJs" width="700" height="999" />\r\n<h1><span style="font-weight: 400;">Liberate the Local Airwaves</span></h1>\r\nFreeform Portland KFFP-LP 90.3 FM is run by a dedicated group of volunteers, music enthusiasts and DJs from Portland, Oregon who want to reclaim some portion of our airwaves from corporate control. Our station benefits our communities in the following ways:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hosting free public broadcasting classes and music education opportunities</li>\r\n	<li>Featuring a vast and diverse mix of DJs with unique cultural perspectives and fresh voices</li>\r\n	<li>Providing exposure to local and touring musicians</li>\r\n	<li>Broadcasting under-represented experimental music and arts programming</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFreeform Portland is a 501(3)(c) entity, classified by the IRS as a charitable organization. We''re proud to uphold community radio and freeform programming in ways that benefit and deeply resonate with our listeners.\r\n\r\n<a href="/donate/">Donate to KFFP!</a>\r\n\r\nCan''t donate? <a href="/about/volunteer/">Help out!</a>', '', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '5-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-15 22:11:41', '2016-07-15 22:11:41', '', 5, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/5-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(620, 2, '2016-07-15 22:12:51', '2016-07-15 22:12:51', '<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-143" src="http://www.freeformportland.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/thought-crime.jpg" alt="thought-crime" width="700" height="655" />\r\n<h1>About Freeform Portland</h1>\r\nFreeform Portland is a nonprofit, independent, community-driven radio station broadcasting at KFFP-LP 90.3 FM in North Portland and streaming live on <a href="http://www.freeformportland.org/listen">freeformportland.org/listen</a>. Our purpose is to foster independent, local, experimental, and underground music alongside arts and public affairs programming that authentically reflects our communities. Freeform Portland is a 501(3)(c) entity, classified by the IRS as a charitable organization.\r\n<h1>Community-Driven</h1>\r\nWe need more community radio. For a city with a metro area of over two million creative people, Portland has a surprisingly small number of non-commercial, independent radio stations on the air. Three companies control the majority of FM radio stations broadcasting in our city. Community radio provides an invaluable venue for more voices to be heard and more perspectives to be represented in public media. We love local stations like KBOO, KMHD, and XRAY. Freeform Portland is proud to join them in taking back the airwaves from corporate control.\r\n<h1>Freeform Radio</h1>\r\nWhat is freeform radio? Freeform radio is a programming format in which the DJ is given total control over what to play, regardless of music genre or commercial interests. Freeform radio stands in contrast to most commercial radio stations where DJs have little or no influence over programming structure or playlists. Ken Freedman from WFMU (the longest-running freeform radio station in the United States) explains the importance of freeform radio and what Freeform Portland is up to <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z-qEUkYWnck" target="_blank">here</a>.\r\n<h1></h1>', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '13-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-15 22:12:51', '2016-07-15 22:12:51', '', 13, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/13-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(146, 1, '2016-03-11 19:42:10', '2016-03-11 19:42:10', '<h1>Donate</h1>\r\n\r\nFreeform Portland is a 501(3)c nonprofit organization benefiting our community through providing a number of public resources:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Broadcasting Musicology classes</li>\r\n	<li>Music library</li>\r\n	<li>Promoting local music and arts events</li>\r\n	<li>More!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nOur station runs on volunteer and financial support from our friends and neighbors and we are grateful for any and all contributions.\r\n\r\nYour donation to Freeform Portland can be tax-deductible!\r\n\r\n<p><form action="https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr" method="post" target="_top"><input type="hidden" name="cmd" value="_s-xclick"><input type="hidden" name="hosted_button_id" value="EXDPWNQFGWYEL"><input type="image" src="https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/btn/btn_donate_LG.gif" border="0" name="submit" alt="Donate to KFFP"></form></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Feel free to send a check, if  you''d like. Please make checks out to Freeform Portland and mail to:\r\nFreeform Portland\r\n801 N. Killingsworth St.\r\nPortland OR 97217</p>\r\nFreeform Portland will gratefully accept your donation of records, CDs and headphones in good working condition, plus office supplies, snacks, and more — please email donate@freeformportland.org to get in touch with a donations volunteer. You can also keep an eye out for the donation jar at most KFFP events.\r\n\r\nThanks so much!', 'Donate', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '32-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-11 19:42:10', '2016-03-11 19:42:10', '', 32, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/32-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
