(601, 3, '2016-10-07 16:24:39', '2016-10-07 16:24:39', '<img class="alignnone wp-image-881 size-full" src="http://www.freeformportland.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/15.jpg" alt="" width="759" height="366" />\r\n<h1>October 1 – 7 Donor Drive</h1>\r\nFreeform Portland is kicking off a <a href="http://www.freeformportland.org/drive/">donor drive</a> on October 1st, and we’re offering one-of-a-kind gifts for donations made during the week of October 1 – 7! Help us stay on air, improve our broadcast signal, and continue to offer unique opportunities and services to the Portland community. <a href="http://www.freeformportland.org/drive/">Click here</a> to donate and learn more about the October Donor Drive.\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 16px;">Freeform Portland KFFP-LP 90.3 FM is run by a dedicated group of music enthusiasts and DJs from Portland, Oregon. We''re local volunteers who want to reclaim some portion of our airwaves from corporate control.</span>\r\n\r\nWe offer:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Public broadcasting classes and music education opportunities</li>\r\n	<li>DJs with unique cultural perspectives and fresh voices from the local community</li>\r\n	<li>Exposure to local and touring musicians</li>\r\n	<li>Experimental music and arts programming, under-represented in Portland</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nLet''s uphold community radio and freeform programming that truly reflects and celebrates our local communities.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', '', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '5-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-10-07 16:24:39', '2016-10-07 16:24:39', '', 5, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/5-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(645, 2, '2016-07-25 00:42:38', '2016-07-25 00:42:38', '<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-580" src="http://www.freeformportland.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Record-Player-II_Nick-Pennell.jpg" alt="Freeform Portland Vinyl DJs" width="700" height="999" />\r\n<h1><span style="font-weight: 400;">Liberate the Local Airwaves</span></h1>\r\nFreeform Portland KFFP-LP 90.3 FM is run by a dedicated group of music enthusiasts and DJs from Portland, Oregon. We''re local volunteers who want to reclaim some portion of our airwaves from corporate control.\r\n\r\nWe offer:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Public broadcasting classes and music education opportunities</li>\r\n	<li>DJs with unique cultural perspectives and fresh voices from the local community</li>\r\n	<li>Exposure to local and touring musicians</li>\r\n	<li>Experimental music and arts programming, under-represented in Portland</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nLet''s uphold community radio and freeform programming that truly reflects and celebrates our local communities.\r\n\r\n<a href="/donate/">Donate to KFFP!</a>\r\n\r\nCan''t donate? <a href="/about/volunteer/">Help out!</a>', '', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '5-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-25 00:42:38', '2016-07-25 00:42:38', '', 5, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/5-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(618, 2, '2016-07-15 22:06:18', '2016-07-15 22:06:18', '<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-580" src="http://www.freeformportland.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Record-Player-II_Nick-Pennell.jpg" alt="Freeform Portland Vinyl DJs" width="700" height="999" />\r\n<h1><span style="font-weight: 400;">Liberate the Local Airwaves</span></h1>\r\nFreeform Portland KFFP-LP 90.3 FM is run by a dedicated group of volunteer music enthusiasts and DJs from Portland, Oregon who want to reclaim some portion of our airwaves from corporate control. Our station benefits our communities in the following ways:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hosting free public broadcasting classes and music education opportunities</li>\r\n	<li>Featuring a vast and diverse mix of DJs with unique cultural perspectives and fresh voices</li>\r\n	<li>Providing exposure to local and touring musicians</li>\r\n	<li>Broadcasting under-represented experimental music and arts programming</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFreeform Portland is a 501(3)(c) entity, classified by the IRS as a charitable organization. We''re proud to uphold community radio and freeform programming in ways that benefit and deeply resonate with our listeners.\r\n\r\n<a href="/donate/">Donate to KFFP!</a>\r\n\r\nCan''t donate? <a href="/about/volunteer/">Help out!</a>', '', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '5-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-07-15 22:06:18', '2016-07-15 22:06:18', '', 5, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/5-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(602, 3, '2016-06-25 07:09:22', '2016-06-25 07:09:22', '<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-580" src="http://www.freeformportland.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Record-Player-II_Nick-Pennell.jpg" alt="Freeform Portland Vinyl DJs" width="700" height="999" />\r\n<h1><span style="font-weight: 400;">Liberate the Local Airwaves</span></h1>\r\nFreeform Portland KFFP-LP 90.3 FM is run by a dedicated group of volunteer music enthusiasts and DJs from Portland, Oregon who want to reclaim some portion of our airwaves from corporate control. Our station benefits our communities in the following ways:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hosting free public broadcasting classes and musical educational opportunities</li>\r\n	<li>Featuring a vast and diverse mix of DJs with unique cultural perspectives and fresh voices</li>\r\n	<li>Providing exposure to local and touring musicians</li>\r\n	<li>Broadcasting experimental music and arts programming, which we believe are under-represented in Portland</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFreeform Portland is a 501(3)(c) entity, classified by the IRS as a charitable organization. We''re proud to uphold community radio and freeform programming in ways that benefit and deeply resonate with our listeners.\r\n\r\n<a href="/donate/">Donate to KFFP!</a>\r\n\r\nCan''t donate? <a href="/about/volunteer/">Help out!</a>', '', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '5-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-25 07:09:22', '2016-06-25 07:09:22', '', 5, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/5-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(151, 1, '2016-03-11 19:46:28', '2016-03-11 19:46:28', '<h1 style="text-align: center">FAQ</h1>\r\n\r\n<h3>How can I donate? Are donations tax deductible?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Donations are 501(c)3 tax-deductible. Get a limited edition shirt through our <a href="http://bit.ly/1Hvk1qA">indiegogo</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Why does Portland need another listener-supported radio station?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>3 companies own 75% of our local airwaves. We feel that we have to do something about that. We are working in cooperation with every non-commercial radio station in Portland. Seriously. It''s a team effort. The only way to make radio better in Portland is to keep making better radio in Portland.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>What''s the Frequency, Kenneth? Projected launch date? Where''s the studio?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>With your help we will test FM broadcasting in 2015 and launch in 2016. Please sign up for the email list on this page.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Can I have a show? Will you play my band''s album please?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>More info soon! Please sign up for the email list on this page</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Volunteer opportunities? How can I help?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>email volunteer@freeformportland.org and tell us about yourself.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Will there be commercials? I''ll be able to hear this station from my house /car?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Freeform Portland is a non-profit commercial-free radio station coming to Low-Power FM in Portland in 2016. We''re using the same engineering team that created KZME and XRAY and working alongside every non-commercial radio station in Portland. We''re stoked to get to broadcasting ASAP and we need your help.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-11 19:46:28', '2016-03-11 19:46:28', '', 16, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/16-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(152, 1, '2016-03-11 23:10:58', '2016-03-11 23:10:58', '<h1 style="text-align: center">FAQ</h1>\r\n\r\n<h3>How can I donate? Are donations tax deductible?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Donations are 501(c)3 tax-deductible. Please visit our <a href="/donate/">donation page</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Why does Portland need another listener-supported radio station?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>3 companies own 75% of our local airwaves. We feel that we have to do something about that. We are working in cooperation with every non-commercial radio station in Portland. Seriously. It''s a team effort. The only way to make radio better in Portland is to keep making better radio in Portland.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>What''s the Frequency, Kenneth? Projected launch date? Where''s the studio?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>With your help we will test FM broadcasting in 2015 and launch in 2016. Please sign up for the email list on this page.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Can I have a show? Will you play my band''s album please?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>More info soon! Please sign up for the email list on this page</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Volunteer opportunities? How can I help?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>email volunteer@freeformportland.org and tell us about yourself.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Will there be commercials? I''ll be able to hear this station from my house /car?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Freeform Portland is a non-profit commercial-free radio station coming to Low-Power FM in Portland in 2016. We''re using the same engineering team that created KZME and XRAY and working alongside every non-commercial radio station in Portland. We''re stoked to get to broadcasting ASAP and we need your help.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-11 23:10:58', '2016-03-11 23:10:58', '', 16, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/16-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(603, 3, '2016-06-25 07:16:00', '2016-06-25 07:16:00', '<h1 style="text-align: center;">FAQ</h1>\r\n<h3>How can I donate? Are donations tax deductible?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Yes, donations are tax deductible. Our station has 501(c)(3) status, which means the IRS classifies us as a charitable organization. Freeform Portland gratefully accepts donations through PayPal or by check. We also love donations of records, CDs and headphones in good and working condition. Our station runs on support from our friends and neighbors and we are grateful for any and all contributions! Please visit our <a href="http://www.freeformportland.org/donate/">Donate page</a> for more information.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>What''s the Frequency, Kenneth? How old is the station?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Freeform Portland went on the air at 90.3 FM in north Portland in April 2016. Our full call sign is KFFP-LP 90.3 FM. (The "LP" stands for "low power.")</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Where can I get the best signal for Freeform Portland?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Our transmitter is located in the NE Alberta neighborhood in Portland, OR. We''re a low-power FM station, which means our range has an approximate 5-mile radius. Your reception will vary depending on your equipment, distance from the transmitter, and the height of the buildings in between. We also stream online at <a href="http://www.freeformportland.org/listen">www.freeformportland.org/listen</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Can I have a show?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Yes! All on-air DJs must first complete at least 5 volunteer hours each month, and complete DJ training with Freeform Portland.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>What about volunteer opportunities? How can I help?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Yes, we have <a href="http://www.freeformportland.org/about/volunteer/" target="_blank">many volunteer opportunities</a>. To find out more, please fill out our <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/118lWyMgnMCVz3_xNOwMkUqXjYDnjq3wJPpVorB3BaBk/viewform?c=0&amp;w=1" target="_blank">KFFP Volunteer Contact Form</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Will you play my band''s album?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Most likely! Music adhering to FCC regulations is eligible to be played on our station. Send music to:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFreeform Portland\r\nc/o Music Library\r\n5511 N Albina Ave.\r\nPortland OR 97217\r\n<h3>Are there commercials?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>No! Freeform Portland is a nonprofit, commercial-free radio station. We''re using the same engineering team that created KZME and XRAY and working alongside other non-commercial radio stations in Portland.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Where''s the studio located?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><span style="font-size: 16px;">We''re at 5511 N Albina Ave. in Portland, Oregon. (Our cross street is Killingsworth.)</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Are you selling merch?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Yes, we have a variety of things in stock — normally we have t-shirts, koozies, bottle opener key chains, stickers, and more. Keep an eye out for our merch table at KFFP-sponsored events.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-25 07:16:00', '2016-06-25 07:16:00', '', 16, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/16-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(678, 2, '2016-08-08 23:14:11', '2016-08-08 23:14:11', '<h1 style="text-align: center;">Donate</h1>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;"><input alt="Donate to KFFP" name="submit" src="https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/btn/btn_donate_LG.gif" type="image" /></p>\r\nFreeform Portland KFFP-LP 90.3 FM is run by a dedicated group of volunteer music enthusiasts and DJs from Portland, Oregon who want to reclaim some portion of our airwaves from corporate control. Our station benefits our communities in the following ways:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hosting free public broadcasting classes and musical educational opportunities</li>\r\n	<li>Featuring a vast and diverse mix of DJs with unique cultural perspectives and fresh voices</li>\r\n	<li>Providing exposure to local and touring musicians</li>\r\n	<li>Broadcasting experimental music and arts programming, which we believe are under-represented in Portland</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFreeform Portland is a 501(3)(c) entity, classified by the IRS as a charitable organization. We’re proud to uphold community radio and freeform programming in ways that benefit and deeply resonate with our listeners.\r\n\r\nFeel free to send a check, if  you''d like. Please make checks out to Freeform Portland and mail to:\r\n\r\nFreeform Portland\r\nc/o Donations\r\n5511 N. Albina Ave.\r\nPortland OR 97217\r\n\r\nFreeform Portland will gratefully accept your donation of records, CDs and headphones in good working condition, plus office supplies, snacks, and more — please email donate@freeformportland.org to get in touch with a donations volunteer. You can also keep an eye out for the donation jar at most KFFP events.\r\n\r\nThanks so much!\r\n\r\n— KFFP Volunteers', 'Donate', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '32-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-08 23:14:11', '2016-08-08 23:14:11', '', 32, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/32-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(604, 3, '2016-06-25 07:19:35', '2016-06-25 07:19:35', '<h1 style="text-align: center;">Donate</h1>\r\nFreeform Portland KFFP-LP 90.3 FM is run by a dedicated group of volunteer music enthusiasts and DJs from Portland, Oregon who want to reclaim some portion of our airwaves from corporate control. Our station benefits our communities in the following ways:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Hosting free public broadcasting classes and musical educational opportunities</li>\r\n	<li>Featuring a vast and diverse mix of DJs with unique cultural perspectives and fresh voices</li>\r\n	<li>Providing exposure to local and touring musicians</li>\r\n	<li>Broadcasting experimental music and arts programming, which we believe are under-represented in Portland</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFreeform Portland is a 501(3)(c) entity, classified by the IRS as a charitable organization. We’re proud to uphold community radio and freeform programming in ways that benefit and deeply resonate with our listeners.\r\n\r\n<form action="https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr" method="post" target="_top"><input name="cmd" type="hidden" value="_s-xclick" /><input name="hosted_button_id" type="hidden" value="EXDPWNQFGWYEL" /><input alt="Donate to KFFP" name="submit" src="https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/btn/btn_donate_LG.gif" type="image" /></form>Feel free to send a check, if  you''d like. Please make checks out to Freeform Portland and mail to:\r\n\r\nFreeform Portland\r\nc/o Donations\r\n5511 N. Albina Ave.\r\nPortland OR 97217\r\n\r\nFreeform Portland will gratefully accept your donation of records, CDs and headphones in good working condition, plus office supplies, snacks, and more — please email donate@freeformportland.org to get in touch with a donations volunteer. You can also keep an eye out for the donation jar at most KFFP events.\r\n\r\nThanks so much!\r\n\r\n— KFFP Volunteers', 'Donate', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '32-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-25 07:19:35', '2016-06-25 07:19:35', '', 32, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/32-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(605, 3, '2016-06-25 07:21:17', '2016-06-25 07:21:17', '<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-143" src="http://www.freeformportland.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/thought-crime.jpg" alt="thought-crime" width="700" height="655" />\r\n<h1>About Freeform Portland</h1>\r\nFreeform Portland is a nonprofit, independent, community-driven radio station broadcasting at KFFP-LP 90.3 FM and streaming live on <a href="http://www.freeformportland.org/listen">freeformportland.org/listen</a>. Our purpose is to foster independent, local, experimental, and underground music alongside arts and public affairs programming that authentically reflects our communities. Freeform Portland is a 501(3)(c) entity, classified by the IRS as a charitable organization.\r\n<h1>Community-Driven</h1>\r\nWe need more community radio. For a city with a metro area of over two million creative people, Portland has a surprisingly small number of non-commercial, independent radio stations on the air. Three companies control the majority of FM radio stations broadcasting in our city. Community radio provides an invaluable venue for more voices to be heard and more perspectives to be represented in public media. We love local stations like KBOO, KMHD, and XRAY. Freeform Portland is proud to join them in taking back the airwaves from corporate control.\r\n<h1>Freeform Radio</h1>\r\nWhat is freeform radio? Freeform radio is a programming format in which the DJ is given total control over what to play, regardless of music genre or commercial interests. Freeform radio stands in contrast to most commercial radio stations where DJs have little or no influence over programming structure or playlists. Ken Freedman from WFMU (the longest-running freeform radio station in the United States) explains the importance of freeform radio and what Freeform Portland is up to <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z-qEUkYWnck" target="_blank">here</a>.\r\n<h1></h1>', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '13-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-06-25 07:21:17', '2016-06-25 07:21:17', '', 13, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/13-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
