(332, 23, '2016-06-28 05:46:31', '2016-06-28 05:46:31', 'Morningstar is an eventide ritual, a sonic seance, a crossroads in the dead of night.\\n\\nMorningstar will be drawing sounds and inspiration from all over. Eclectic and unpredictable are the watchwords. A special focus will be given to ritualistic electronica and beat manipulations, but expect to hear film music, especially from horror movies; folk music from all over the world; some metal, the rawer the better; dreamy, psychedelic -gaze; and special themed shows.\\n\\nThere will also be the occasional ragers &amp; bangers, as well, to help you get through the night. Techno, trip metal, rhythmic noise, mnml, house, bass music, balearic, jacked, jersey club, grime, d ''n b, jungle, trip-hop are all on the queue.\\n\\nPhysical media will be used when possible, otherwise sourced from Dessicant''s Akashic Archives.\\n\\nMorningstar. For those who do not fear the darkness, but never stop striving for the light. †', 'Morning Star', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '177-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-06-28 05:46:31', '2016-06-28 05:46:31', '', 177, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/177-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
