(775, 3, '2016-09-29 15:45:49', '2016-09-29 15:45:49', 'Freeform Portland is excited to have the opportunity to support local businesses on air! Your business can receive on-air mentions where we will highlight your goods and services and include your name on our website.  If this interests you, contact <a>underwriting@freeformportland.<wbr />org</a>.\r\n\r\nBelow are general examples of packages that Freeform Portland is offering. The value of Underwriting spots are measured by the time of day that they are shared. The minimum underwriting agreement is 6 months, and we offer extra spots for businesses that sign up for 12 months or longer. We are also able to adjust the number of spots to fit any budget.\r\n<table>\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td colspan="3"><strong>Basic Underwriting On-Air Mentions Per Month</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>$100 per month</td>\r\n<td>$200 per month</td>\r\n<td>$300 per month</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Two spots per week</td>\r\n<td>Four spots per week</td>\r\n<td>Eight spots per week</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>1 Early Morning</td>\r\n<td>2 Early morning</td>\r\n<td>3 Early Morning</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>1 Afternoon</td>\r\n<td>2 Afternoon</td>\r\n<td>2 Afternoon</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td></td>\r\n<td></td>\r\n<td>3 Evening</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\nOr if you want to make a tax-deductible, individual donation, you can do so by clicking <a href="http://www.freeformportland.org/donate/">here</a>.', 'Underwriting', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '707-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-09-29 15:45:49', '2016-09-29 15:45:49', '', 707, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/707-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(802, 2, '2016-09-29 23:04:31', '2016-09-29 23:04:31', '<h1>October 1 - 7 Donor Drive\r\nCelebrating Our First Year</h1>\r\n[Jon, please insert PayPal donate button]\r\n\r\nThis past year Freeform Portland grew from its crowd-funded beginnings in Portland, Oregon to become the creative and educational community of DJs and music lovers that it is today. Over 100 local volunteers now contribute to our unique, diverse programming 24/7, streaming online worldwide at freeformportland.org, and broadcasting locally at 90.3 FM from the Baker Building in North Portland.\r\n\r\nTo celebrate our first year, we''re kicking off a donor drive on October 1st and will offer one-of-a-kind gifts for donations the week of October 1 - 7! <a href="http://www.freeformportland.org/donate/" target="_blank">Donate</a> during the drive and you can receive a limited-run shirt, a special thank you mix by your favorite DJ, a spot co-hosting a radio show, among other exciting offers! See below for a list of our donor drive premiums.\r\n<h1>Help Us Stay Up and Running!</h1>\r\nIn a short amount of time, we''ve already seen exponential growth with our membership and station outreach. We now ask you to consider offering your support during our October Donor Drive. By clicking the Donate button at the top of the page, you''ll personally help us stay on the air, improve our broadcast signal, and continue to offer unique opportunities and services to the Portland community.\r\n\r\nAfter raising $11,000 for our initial launch, we now ask the public to help us raise $15,000 to keep Freeform Portland up and running. Freeform Portland is a 501(3)(c) nonprofit organization, and so your donation is tax deductible. Be sure to check out our special Donor Drive offerings, below! Thank you for listening, participating, and supporting the availability of community freeform radio.\r\n<h1>Premiums for Donating</h1>\r\nIf you <a href="http://www.freeformportland.org/donate/" target="_blank">donate</a> during the October Donor Drive, we''ll send you an email to select one of the special edition gifts listed below to thank you for your donation and support!\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-797 alignleft" src="http://www.freeformportland.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/MockupTshirt-300x280.jpg" alt="MockupTshirt" width="300" height="280" />\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Limited edition Freeform Portland t-shirt for $20+, or $15+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Limited edition Freeform Portland tote bag for $20+, or $15+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Official Freeform Portland hoodie for $40+, or $15 per month</li>\r\n	<li>Your favorite Freeform Portland DJ will DJ your party for a $100+ donation</li>\r\n	<li>Special thank you mix by a Freeform Portland DJ (we''ll email you choices when you donate) for $25+, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>A drawing by The Queen of Siam (The Upstairs Room) for $25+, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Limited edition Deep Lez Power Hour frosted etched glass for $25+, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Limited edition handmade and hand-screenprinted The Guitar and Other Machines record bag for $25+, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Rat tin prepared for you by DJ Mrrranda of Spider in the Ear for $25+, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Limited edition shirt from Teen &amp; Quoz of Terminal Beach for $25+, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Piece of artwork by DJ Zach of Zach''s Radio Show for $25+, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Surprise handmade package from Eeronomicon for $25+, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Artwork by DJ RK Heist from Sounds Obscure for $25+, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of a ransom letter, photos of Rusty Nail in captivity, and special thank you mix by Dusty Dale for $25+, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Limited edition Alleys of Your Mind poster for a $50+ donation</li>\r\n	<li>Tour of Freeform Portland with our radio engineer for a $50+ donation</li>\r\n	<li>Special thank you batch of CDs from Bloodshot Records in Chicago brought to you by DJ HRPunknStuf for $30+, or $15+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Kid sing along of Buffy Vampire the Slayer "Once More, With Feeling" musical verbatim for $25+, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>DJ Zaph Mann''s grab bag of rare CDs for $40+, or $20+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Special merch pack from NONNA of Well Worn and New Territory for a $50+ donation</li>\r\n</ul>', 'Donor Drive', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '772-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-09-29 23:04:31', '2016-09-29 23:04:31', '', 772, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/772-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(244, 61, '2016-03-21 04:17:07', '2016-03-21 04:17:07', 'C’mon, you can guess what it’s like.\r\n\r\nDark ambient, sort of creepy, of course. Post-rock, drone, grindcore, metal… sometimes. Spooky Southern gothic. “Electronica.” J-Pop and klezmer and hot club jazz. Cut-ups and mash-ups. Freak folk, psych rock. A little old-time song and dance number, here and there. Field recordings… Hauntology. Lichenthropy.\r\n\r\nSometimes it’s like getting a lap dance at the butoh performance. Bees in your heart, fleas up your spine.\r\n\r\nRarely painful, more like an intermittent but persistent, muted drumming you can’t quite place. Something “else,” lodged up in there, and you don’t know if it’s digging its way out or digging in.\r\n\r\nSometimes it skips, like a broken thing, like a heartbeat.\r\n\r\nYou know what it’s like, don’t you?', 'Spider in the Ear', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'the-ear-w-mrrranda', '', '', '2017-03-27 20:11:21', '2017-03-28 03:11:21', '', 0, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/?post_type=show&#038;p=244', 0, 'show', '', 0),
(245, 12, '2016-03-21 04:17:49', '2016-03-21 04:17:49', 'A clinic on psychedelic rock, stoner metal, krautrock, progressive rock and related and semi-related genres with an international bent. All of that and more inter-cut with the ramblings of an antisocial music nerd and audio clips that make you think/laugh. 20+ minute long musical explorations being more common than your standard 2-3 minute pop song, with a hefty dose of unsigned and self promoted bands. Also features special episodes that diverge greatly from the norm.', 'Dr. Fuzz''s Heavy Psychedelic Experience', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'heavy-psychedelic-experience-w-dr-fuzz', '', '', '2017-03-27 18:17:44', '2017-03-28 01:17:44', '', 0, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/?post_type=show&#038;p=245', 0, 'show', '', 0),
