(301, 23, '2016-03-25 03:56:33', '2016-03-25 03:56:33', 'The word Nocturne is defined by The Oxford Advanced Learner''s Dictionary as a \\"short composition of a romantic or dreamy character suggestive of night, typically for piano.\\" This definition of Nocturne dates back to 19th century chamber music, which was played in a lyrical, melancholy sort of way. The type of music I am interested in playing has little to do with 19th Century chamber music, however I am interested in exploring the idea of night music, of creating a show based around a feeling, a quality of light. \\nMy Nocturne would strive to redefine the genre for a contemporary audience, focusing on abstract, moody, and poetic, experimental music. It would be a show for the last hours of night or for the first hours of morning. I would use the lateness of the show to create a context for the music. Nocurne would be a place where the “romantic” and “dreamy character” of minimalist composers like Terry Riley or La Monte Young could come into contact with the contemporary experimental electronics of Lawrence English or Tim Hecker. The focus would be on texture, mood, and abstraction instead of structure or genre. \\nI am also interested in using the show as a sort of showcase for local musicians who are working in the same vain. I would love the show to host monthly live performances of experimental Portland artists specially tailored to fit into the theme and atmosphere that Nocturne would strive to create.', 'Nocturne', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '178-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-03-25 03:56:33', '2016-03-25 03:56:33', '', 178, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/178-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
