(545, 2, '2016-04-11 22:08:18', '2016-04-11 22:08:18', '<h1 style="text-align: center;">FAQ</h1>\r\n<h3>How can I donate? Are donations tax deductible?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Freeform Portland gratefully accepts donations through PayPal or by check. We are pending approval of our 501(c)(3) status for donations. We also love donations of records, CDs and headphones in good and working condition. Our station runs on support from our friends and neighbors and we are grateful for any and all contributions! Please visit our <a href="http://www.freeformportland.org/donate/">Donate page</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>What''s the Frequency, Kenneth? Projected launch date?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Stay tuned for more information on our frequency! Our planned on-air date is Friday, April 1, 2016.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Where can I get the best signal for Freeform Portland?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Our transmitter is located in the NE Alberta neighborhood in Portland, OR. We''re a low power FM station, which means our range has an approximate 5 mile radius. We''ll also be streaming online at freeformportland.org.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Can I have a show?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Yes! All on-air DJs must first complete at least 5 volunteer hours each month, and a DJ training with Freeform Portland.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>What about volunteer opportunities? How can I help?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Yes, we have <a href="http://www.freeformportland.org/about/volunteer/" target="_blank">many volunteer opportunities</a>. To find out more, please fill out our <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/118lWyMgnMCVz3_xNOwMkUqXjYDnjq3wJPpVorB3BaBk/viewform?c=0&amp;w=1" target="_blank">KFFP Volunteer Contact Form</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Will you play my band''s album?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Most likely! Music adhering to FCC regulations is eligible to be played on our station. Send music to:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFreeform Portland\r\nc/o Music Library\r\n801 N. Killingsworth St.\r\nPortland OR 97217\r\n<h3>Will there be commercials?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>No! Freeform Portland is a non-profit, commercial-free radio station. We''re using the same engineering team that created KZME and XRAY and working alongside other non-commercial radio stations in Portland.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Where''s the studio located?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>We''re at 801 N. Killingsworth St. in Portland, Oregon.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-04-11 22:08:18', '2016-04-11 22:08:18', '', 16, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/16-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
