r\n<h3>Will you play my band''s album?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Most likely! Music adhering to FCC regulations is eligible to be played on our station. Send music to:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nFreeform Portland\r\nc/o Music Library\r\n801 N. Killingsworth St.\r\nPortland OR 97217\r\n<h3>Will there be commercials?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>No! Freeform Portland is a non-profit, commercial-free radio station. We''re using the same engineering team that created KZME and XRAY and working alongside other non-commercial radio stations in Portland.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Where''s the studio located?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>We''re at 801 N. Killingsworth St. in Portland, Oregon.</li>\r\n</ul>', 'FAQ', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-31 08:01:23', '2016-03-31 08:01:23', '', 16, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/16-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(557, 2, '2016-04-15 22:35:15', '2016-04-15 22:35:15', '<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-143" src="http://www.freeformportland.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/thought-crime.jpg" alt="thought-crime" width="700" height="655" />\r\n<h1>About Freeform Portland</h1>\r\nFreeform Portland is a nonprofit, independent, community-driven radio station broadcasting soon on Portland''s FM dial. Our purpose is to foster independent, local, experimental, and underground music alongside arts and public affairs programming that authentically reflects our communities.\r\n<h1>Community-Driven</h1>\r\nWe need more community radio. For a city with a metro area of over two million creative people, Portland has a surprisingly small amount of non-commercial, independent radio stations on the air. Three companies control the majority of FM radio stations broadcasting in our city. Community radio provides an invaluable venue for more voices to be heard and more perspectives to be represented in public media. We love local stations like KBOO, KMHD, and XRAY. Freeform Portland is proud to join them in taking back the airwaves from corporate control.\r\n<h1>Freeform Radio</h1>\r\nWhat is freeform radio? Freeform radio is a programming format in which the DJ is given total control over what to play, regardless of music genre or commercial interests. Freeform radio stands in contrast to most commercial radio stations where DJs have little or no influence over programming structure or playlists. Ken Freedman from WFMU (the longest running freeform radio station in the United States) explains the importance of freeform radio and what Freeform Portland is up to <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z-qEUkYWnck" target="_blank">here</a>.\r\n<h1></h1>', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '13-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-04-15 22:35:15', '2016-04-15 22:35:15', '', 13, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/13-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(442, 2, '2016-03-31 08:12:09', '2016-03-31 08:12:09', '<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-143" src="http://www.freeformportland.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/thought-crime.jpg" alt="thought-crime" width="700" height="655" />\r\n<h1>About Freeform Portland</h1>\r\nFreeform Portland is a nonprofit, independent, community-driven radio station broadcasting broadcasting soon on Portland''s FM dial. Our purpose is to foster independent, local, experimental, and underground music alongside arts and public affairs programming that authentically reflects our communities.\r\n<h1>Community-Driven</h1>\r\nWe need more community radio. For a city with a metro area of over two million creative people, Portland has a surprisingly small amount of non-commercial, independent radio stations on the air. The vast majority of radio stations broadcasting in our city are controlled by ClearChannel/iHeartMedia. Community radio provides an invaluable venue for more voices to be heard and more perspectives to be represented in public media. We love local stations like KBOO, KMHD, and XRAY. Freeform Portland is proud to join them in taking back the airwaves from corporate control.\r\n<h1>Freeform Radio</h1>\r\nWhat is freeform radio? Freeform radio is a programming format in which the DJ is given total control over what to play, regardless of music genre or commercial interests. Freeform radio stands in contrast to most commercial radio stations where DJs have little or no influence over programming structure or playlists. Ken Freedman from WFMU (the longest running freeform radio station in the United States) explains the importance of freeform radio and what Freeform Portland is up to <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Z-qEUkYWnck" target="_blank">here</a>.\r\n<h1></h1>', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '13-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-31 08:12:09', '2016-03-31 08:12:09', '', 13, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/13-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(443, 2, '2016-08-08 23:35:15', '2016-08-08 23:35:15', '<h1 style="text-align: center;">Donate</h1>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="https://www.paypal.com/us/cgi-bin/webscr?cmd=_flow&amp;SESSION=ETpls-fsawDeCSuaqZUJ9xRsBJVuAUQhJiLLyhXaPLzfhDlAsLdSSr9pGLO&amp;dispatch=5885d80a13c0db1f8e263663d3faee8de2b8031b89187c030b37e57608011f58" target="_blank"><input alt="Donate to KFFP" name="submit" src="https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/btn/btn_donate_LG.gif" type="image" /></a></p>\nFreeform Portland is a 501(3)(c) organization gratefully accepting tax-deductible donations through <a href="https://www.paypal.com/us/cgi-bin/webscr?cmd=_flow&amp;SESSION=ETpls-fsawDeCSuaqZUJ9xRsBJVuAUQhJiLLyhXaPLzfhDlAsLdSSr9pGLO&amp;dispatch=5885d80a13c0db1f8e263663d3faee8de2b8031b89187c030b37e57608011f58" target="_blank">PayPal</a> or by check. You can also keep an eye out for the donation jar at our events. Please make any checks out to "Freeform Portland" and mail to:\n\nFreeform Portland\nc/o Donations\n5511 N. Albina Ave.\nPortland OR 97217\n\nWe also love donations of records, CDs and headphones in good working condition, plus office supplies, snacks, and more. If you''d like to make a donation like this, please email donate@freeformportland.org to get in touch. Our station runs on support from our friends and neighbors and we appreciate any and all contributions!\n\nFreeform Portland KFFP-LP 90.3 FM benefits our communities in the following ways:\n<ul>\n	<li>Hosting free public broadcasting classes and music education opportunities</li>\n	<li>Featuring a vast and diverse mix of DJs with unique cultural perspectives and fresh voices</li>\n	<li>Providing exposure to local and touring musicians</li>\n	<li>Broadcasting experimental music and arts programming, which we believe are under-represented in Portland</li>\n</ul>\nWe’re proud to uphold community radio and freeform programming in ways that benefit and deeply resonate with our listeners.\n\nThanks so much!\n\n— KFFP Volunteers', 'Donate', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '32-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-08-08 23:35:15', '2016-08-08 23:35:15', '', 32, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/32-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(444, 2, '2016-03-31 08:19:41', '2016-03-31 08:19:41', '<h1 style="text-align: center;">Donate</h1>\r\nFreeform Portland is a nonprofit organization, pending 501(3)c status, benefiting our community through providing a number of public resources:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Broadcast and Musicology classes</li>\r\n	<li>Music library</li>\r\n	<li>Local music and arts events</li>\r\n	<li>More!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nOur station runs on volunteer and financial support from our friends and neighbors and we are grateful for any and all contributions.\r\n<!-- Your donation to Freeform Portland can be tax-deductible! -->\r\n\r\n<form action="https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr" method="post" target="_top"><input name="cmd" type="hidden" value="_s-xclick" /><input name="hosted_button_id" type="hidden" value="EXDPWNQFGWYEL" /><input alt="Donate to KFFP" name="submit" src="https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/btn/btn_donate_LG.gif" type="image" /></form>Feel free to send a check, if  you''d like. Please make checks out to Freeform Portland and mail to:\r\n\r\nFreeform Portland\r\nc/o Donations\r\n801 N. Killingsworth St.\r\nPortland OR 97217\r\n\r\nFreeform Portland will gratefully accept your donation of records, CDs and headphones in good working condition, plus office supplies, snacks, and more — please email donate@freeformportland.org to get in touch with a donations volunteer. You can also keep an eye out for the donation jar at most KFFP events.\r\n\r\nThanks so much!\r\n\r\n-- KFFP Volunteers', 'Donate', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '32-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-03-31 08:19:41', '2016-03-31 08:19:41', '', 32, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/32-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(445, 2, '2016-08-08 23:10:03', '2016-08-08 23:10:03', '<h2>Become a Freeform Portland Volunteer!</h2>\nAnnouncement: We’re NOW accepting DJ show applications for our October 2016 to March 2017 schedule! Fill out a Weekly Show Request Form <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeaBCShJgFkNCzL5NUeGP7RfOgYHZr3RKKtcItMsLI7qfGmyA/viewform" target="_blank">here</a>. The deadline for submissions is August 20, 2016.\n\nFreeform Portland, KFFP-LP 90.30 FM, is a nonprofit, volunteer-run community radio station providing a number of public resources. Interested in becoming a Freeform Portland volunteer? Our volunteers gain job skills, learn about music, and meet new people all while giving back to their communities. It’s a great opportunity for people with a little bit of free time and a lot to gain. Our volunteer committees power the station in the following ways:\n<ul>\n	<li>Broadcasting Operations</li>\n	<li>Grant Writing</li>\n	<li>Fundraising/Events</li>\n	<li>Marketing</li>\n	<li>Music Library</li>\n	<li>Volunteer</li>\n	<li>Website</li>\n	<li>Zine</li>\n</ul>\nRead more about each committee below, and fill out our <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeMMp97qi8aU429o-u_zS51cR15UrYUI7bIXFb5t9ZtLr7g6g/viewform?c=0&amp;w=1" target="_blank">KFFP Volunteer Contact Form</a> to be contacted by a member of our Volunteer Committee.\n\n<span style="color: #111111; font-family: Bitter, Georgia, ''Hiragino Mincho ProN'', ''Yu Mincho'', Meiryo, serif; font-size: 18px; letter-spacing: -0.01em; line-height: 1.3;">Broadcasting Operations / Studio</span>\n\nResponsibilities include maintaining the station''s transmitter, turntables, microphones, wiring, and everything else that counts as broadcasting equipment. Members also collect and organize supplies for KFFP office operations.\n<h3>Grant Writing</h3>\nGrant writers obtain the vast majority of Freeform Portland''s financial support by soliciting grants from donor organizations. Good letter-writers should apply!\n<h3>Fundraising/Events</h3>\nThis group plans and puts on shows, parties, DJ nights, and other events that help bring much-needed funds to KFFP. Members also help develop and distribute merch like t-shirts, pins, koozies, and more.\n<h3>Marketing</h3>\nHelp raise community awareness of our station to bring in new listeners.\n<h3>Music Library</h3>\nThis group keeps the music library stocked, organized, and in good working condition. Music Library Committee volunteers send music requests to record labels and tag new additions to help the KFFP community find what we''re looking for.\n<h3>Volunteer</h3>\nWe always need new volunteers! This committee finds fresh meat and places people where they can be the most comfortable and effective at helping us out.\n<h3>Website</h3>\nVolunteers with website development skills (coding, project planning, etc.) should consider joining this committee. This is the crew that designs the site, writes the content, and develops the features like our streaming music player.\n<h3>Zine</h3>\nThe Zine Committee solicits and creates art and copy, for our lovely Freeform Portland zine, and then publishes and distributes it four times per year for 25 cents an issue.\n\n<hr />\n\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Volunteering with us is a requirement for all of our on-air DJs. Don’t want to be on the air? No problem! Not everyone does, and we can still use your help. To learn more about volunteering with us, fill out the <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/118lWyMgnMCVz3_xNOwMkUqXjYDnjq3wJPpVorB3BaBk/viewform?c=0&amp;w=1">KFFP Volunteer Contact Form</a> or email </span><a href="mailto:volunteer@freeformportland.org"><span style="font-weight: 400;">volunteer@freeformportland.org</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Freeform Portland also accepts </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">donations</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">!</span>', 'Volunteer', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '57-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-08-08 23:10:03', '2016-08-08 23:10:03', '', 57, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/57-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
