(496, 3, '2016-10-04 00:45:53', '2016-10-04 00:45:53', 'Mostly black metal, some other stuff\n\n<blockquote>\n<div>Hence loathed Melancholy,</div>\n<div>Of Cerberus, and blackest Midnight born,</div>\n<div>In Stygian cave forlorn,</div>\n<div>      ''Mongst horrid shapes, and shrieks, and sights unholy;</div>\n<div>Find out some uncouth cell,</div>\n<div>      Where brooding Darkness spreads his jealous wings,</div>\n<div>And the night-raven sings;</div>\n<div>      There under ebon shades, and low-brow''d rocks,</div>\n<div>As ragged as thy locks,</div>\n<div>      In dark Cimmerian desert ever dwell.</div></blockquote>\n<div style="padding-left: 30px;">— excerpt from L''Allegro by John Milton, 1645</div>', 'Black Castle', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '191-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-10-04 00:45:53', '2016-10-04 00:45:53', '', 191, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/191-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(497, 3, '2016-04-06 05:12:45', '2016-04-06 05:12:45', 'Each week you get either a live broadcast from Beech Street Parlor, or from The Soup Caves... deep inside Another Planet.\n<div>Zaph Mann''s IMOJP (In Memory Of John Peel) Show, adheres to the style and values of the late great DJ John Peel: Breaking edgy new music from outside the mainstream in a mesmerising mix of genres. Often #1 in the worldwide freeform charts, selected the best show *anywhere* to here new music by the UK''s Louder Than War - you won''t like it all, but you''ll hear something special, ahead of the crowd.</div>', 'Live from Beech St Parlor / Zaph Mann''s IMOJP Show', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '165-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-04-06 05:12:45', '2016-04-06 05:12:45', '', 165, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/165-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
