(693, 2, '2016-08-10 20:09:24', '2016-08-10 20:09:24', '<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-580" src="http://www.freeformportland.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/01/Record-Player-II_Nick-Pennell.jpg" alt="Freeform Portland Vinyl DJs" width="700" height="999" />\r\n<h1><span style="font-weight: 400;">Liberate the Local Airwaves</span></h1>\r\nFreeform Portland KFFP-LP 90.3 FM is run by a dedicated group of music enthusiasts and DJs from Portland, Oregon. We''re local volunteers who want to reclaim some portion of our airwaves from corporate control.\r\n\r\nWe offer:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Public broadcasting classes and music education opportunities</li>\r\n	<li>DJs with unique cultural perspectives and fresh voices from the local community</li>\r\n	<li>Exposure to local and touring musicians</li>\r\n	<li>Experimental music and arts programming, under-represented in Portland</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nLet''s uphold community radio and freeform programming that truly reflects and celebrates our local communities.\r\n\r\n<a href="/donate/">Donate to KFFP!</a>\r\n\r\nCan''t donate? <a href="/about/volunteer/">Help out!</a>\r\n\r\n<em>We’re NOW accepting DJ show applications for our October 2016 to March 2017 schedule! Fill out a <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeaBCShJgFkNCzL5NUeGP7RfOgYHZr3RKKtcItMsLI7qfGmyA/viewform" target="_blank">Weekly Show Request Form here</a>. The deadline for submissions is August 20, 2016.</em>', '', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '5-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-10 20:09:24', '2016-08-10 20:09:24', '', 5, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/5-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(694, 2, '2016-08-10 20:09:49', '2016-08-10 20:09:49', '<h2>Become a Freeform Portland Volunteer!</h2>\r\n<em>We’re NOW accepting DJ show applications for our October 2016 to March 2017 schedule! Fill out a <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeaBCShJgFkNCzL5NUeGP7RfOgYHZr3RKKtcItMsLI7qfGmyA/viewform" target="_blank">Weekly Show Request Form here</a>. The deadline for submissions is August 20, 2016.</em>\r\n\r\nFreeform Portland, KFFP-LP 90.30 FM, is a nonprofit, volunteer-run community radio station providing a number of public resources. Interested in becoming a Freeform Portland volunteer? Our volunteers gain job skills, learn about music, and meet new people all while giving back to their communities. It’s a great opportunity for people with a little bit of free time and a lot to gain. Our volunteer committees power the station in the following ways:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Broadcasting Operations</li>\r\n	<li>Grant Writing</li>\r\n	<li>Fundraising/Events</li>\r\n	<li>Marketing</li>\r\n	<li>Music Library</li>\r\n	<li>Volunteer</li>\r\n	<li>Website</li>\r\n	<li>Zine</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nRead more about each committee below, and fill out our <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLSeMMp97qi8aU429o-u_zS51cR15UrYUI7bIXFb5t9ZtLr7g6g/viewform?c=0&amp;w=1" target="_blank">KFFP Volunteer Contact Form</a> to be contacted by a member of our Volunteer Committee.\r\n<h3>Broadcasting Operations</h3>\r\nResponsibilities include maintaining the station''s transmitter, turntables, microphones, wiring, and everything else that counts as broadcasting equipment. Members also collect and organize supplies for KFFP office operations.\r\n<h3>Grant Writing</h3>\r\nGrant writers obtain the vast majority of Freeform Portland''s financial support by soliciting grants from donor organizations. Good letter-writers should apply!\r\n<h3>Fundraising/Events</h3>\r\nThis group plans and puts on shows, parties, DJ nights, and other events that help bring much-needed funds to KFFP. Members also help develop and distribute merch like t-shirts, pins, koozies, and more.\r\n<h3>Marketing</h3>\r\nHelp raise community awareness of our station to bring in new listeners.\r\n<h3>Music Library</h3>\r\nThis group keeps the music library stocked, organized, and in good working condition. Music Library Committee volunteers send music requests to record labels and tag new additions to help the KFFP community find what we''re looking for.\r\n<h3>Volunteer</h3>\r\nWe always need new volunteers! This committee finds fresh meat and places people where they can be the most comfortable and effective at helping us out.\r\n<h3>Website</h3>\r\nVolunteers with website development skills (coding, project planning, etc.) should consider joining this committee. This is the crew that designs the site, writes the content, and develops the features like our streaming music player.\r\n<h3>Zine</h3>\r\nThe Zine Committee solicits and creates art and copy, for our lovely Freeform Portland zine, and then publishes and distributes it four times per year for 25 cents an issue.\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\n<span style="font-weight: 400;">Volunteering with us is a requirement for all of our on-air DJs. Don’t want to be on the air? No problem! Not everyone does, and we can still use your help. To learn more about volunteering with us, fill out the <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/118lWyMgnMCVz3_xNOwMkUqXjYDnjq3wJPpVorB3BaBk/viewform?c=0&amp;w=1">KFFP Volunteer Contact Form</a> or email </span><a href="mailto:volunteer@freeformportland.org"><span style="font-weight: 400;">volunteer@freeformportland.org</span></a><span style="font-weight: 400;">. Freeform Portland also accepts </span><span style="font-weight: 400;"><a href="http://www.freeformportland.org/donate/" target="_blank">donations</a></span><span style="font-weight: 400;">!</span>', 'Volunteer', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '57-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-08-10 20:09:49', '2016-08-10 20:09:49', '', 57, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/57-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(699, 2, '2016-08-18 23:33:18', '2016-08-18 23:33:18', 'Aurora: A step into the world of sound art and tangential sonic histories. This show focuses on sound artists and their influence on contemporary music and technology.\n\nNocturne: The word Nocturne is defined by The Oxford Advanced Learner''s Dictionary as a "short composition of a romantic or dreamy character suggestive of night, typically for piano." This definition of Nocturne dates back to 19th century chamber music, which was played in a lyrical, melancholy sort of way. The type of music I am interested in playing has little to do with 19th Century chamber music, however I am interested in exploring the idea of night music, of creating a show based around a feeling, a quality of light.\n\nMy Nocturne would strive to redefine the genre for a contemporary audience, focusing on abstract, moody, and poetic, experimental music. It would be a show for the last hours of night or for the first hours of morning. I would use the lateness of the show to create a context for the music. Nocurne would be a place where the “romantic” and “dreamy character” of minimalist composers like Terry Riley or La Monte Young could come into contact with the contemporary experimental electronics of Lawrence English or Tim Hecker. The focus would be on texture, mood, and abstraction instead of structure or genre.\n\nI am also interested in using the show as a sort of showcase for local musicians who are working in the same vain. I would love the show to host monthly live performances of experimental Portland artists specially tailored to fit into the theme and atmosphere that Nocturne would strive to create.', 'Nocturne / Aurora (Alternating)', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '178-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-08-18 23:33:18', '2016-08-18 23:33:18', '', 178, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/178-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(872, 3, '2016-10-05 15:05:44', '2016-10-05 15:05:44', '<a href="/drive"><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-580" src="/images/meter/8.jpg" alt="Freeform Portland Vinyl DJs" width="700" height="999" /></a>\r\n<h1>October 1 – 7 Donor Drive</h1>\r\nFreeform Portland is kicking off a <a href="http://www.freeformportland.org/drive/">donor drive</a> on October 1st, and we’re offering one-of-a-kind gifts for donations made during the week of October 1 – 7! Help us stay on air, improve our broadcast signal, and continue to offer unique opportunities and services to the Portland community. <a href="http://www.freeformportland.org/drive/">Click here</a> to donate and learn more about the October Donor Drive.\r\n\r\n<span style="font-size: 16px;">Freeform Portland KFFP-LP 90.3 FM is run by a dedicated group of music enthusiasts and DJs from Portland, Oregon. We''re local volunteers who want to reclaim some portion of our airwaves from corporate control.</span>\r\n\r\nWe offer:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Public broadcasting classes and music education opportunities</li>\r\n	<li>DJs with unique cultural perspectives and fresh voices from the local community</li>\r\n	<li>Exposure to local and touring musicians</li>\r\n	<li>Experimental music and arts programming, under-represented in Portland</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nLet''s uphold community radio and freeform programming that truly reflects and celebrates our local communities.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', '', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '5-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-05 15:05:44', '2016-10-05 15:05:44', '', 5, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/5-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(702, 2, '2016-08-19 22:46:19', '2016-08-19 22:46:19', 'Turtles Have Short Legs: An intoxicating mix of psychedelic and experimental sounds, past and present. Expect krautrock/kosmische nuggets, modal acid folk &amp; weirdlore, hauntological delights, pop-sike pipe-dreams, radiophonics &amp; analog electronics, surreal sound collages &amp; drones, progressive/avant-rock oddities and unusual international sounds. With DJ gilliflower &amp; eeronomicon\n\nFrankenstein''s Footlocker: A rambling, oddball collection of records, stories, comedy, cover songs, found audio, sound collages, and original in-studio performances. Frankenstein''s Footlocker has it all,  from thematic trips through music history to artistic free-for-alls. When the footlocker creaks open, you''ll be entertained, amazed, and educated.', 'Turtles Have Short Legs  / Frankenstein''s Footlocker (Alternating)', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '164-autosave-v1', '', '', '2016-08-19 22:46:19', '2016-08-19 22:46:19', '', 164, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/164-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
