(772, 2, '2016-09-28 06:01:23', '2016-09-28 06:01:23', '<h1>October 1 - 7 Donor Drive\r\nCelebrating Our First Year</h1>\r\n<form style="margin-bottom: 1em;" action="https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr" method="post" target="_top"><input name="cmd" type="hidden" value="_s-xclick" /><input name="hosted_button_id" type="hidden" value="EXDPWNQFGWYEL" /><input alt="Donate to KFFP" name="submit" src="https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/btn/btn_donate_LG.gif" type="image" /></form>\r\n\r\n[caption id="attachment_854" align="alignright" width="221"]<img class="wp-image-854 size-medium" src="http://www.freeformportland.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/the-hunger-is-real-melissa-chalhoub-for-Freeform-PDX-221x300.jpg" alt="the hunger is real - melissa chalhoub for Freeform PDX" width="221" height="300" /> by Mélissa Chalhoub[/caption]\r\n\r\nOver the past year Freeform Portland grew from its crowd-funded beginnings in Portland, Oregon to become the creative and educational community of DJs and music lovers that it is today. Over 100 local volunteers now contribute to our unique, diverse programming 24/7, streaming online worldwide at freeformportland.org, and broadcasting locally at 90.3 FM from the Baker Building in North Portland.\r\n\r\nTo celebrate our first year we''re kicking off a donor drive on October 1st, and we''re offering one-of-a-kind gifts for donations made during the week of October 1 - 7! See below for a list of our donor drive premiums.\r\n<h1>Help Us Stay Up and Running!</h1>\r\nAfter raising $11,000 for our initial launch, we now ask listeners and our community to help us raise $15,000 to keep Freeform Portland up and running. By clicking the Donate button at the top of the page you''ll personally help us stay on air, improve our broadcast signal, and continue to offer unique opportunities and services to the Portland community. We''re a 501(3)(c) nonprofit organization, and so your donation is tax deductible.\r\n\r\nThank you for listening, participating, and supporting the availability of community freeform radio. Be sure to check out our special Donor Drive offerings, below!\r\n<h1>Premiums for Donating</h1>\r\n<strong>If you donate during the October Donor Drive, we''ll send you an email to select one of the special edition gifts listed below to thank you for your donation and support!\r\n</strong>For each item, there is a one-time donation option listed first, and then many items include a monthly donation as another choice.\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-medium wp-image-797 alignleft" src="http://www.freeformportland.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/MockupTshirt-300x280.jpg" alt="MockupTshirt" width="300" height="280" />\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Limited edition Freeform Portland t-shirt for $20+ donation, or $15+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Limited edition Freeform Portland tote bag for $20+ donation, or $15+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Official Freeform Portland hoodie for $40+ donation, or $15+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Your favorite Freeform Portland DJ will DJ your party for a $100+ donation</li>\r\n	<li>Co-host a show on Freeform Portland for a $100+ donation</li>\r\n	<li>Tour of Freeform Portland studio with technical explanations by our radio engineer for a $50+ donation</li>\r\n	<li>Special thank you mix by a Freeform Portland DJ (we''ll email you choices when you donate) for $25+ donation, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Limited edition Alleys of Your Mind <a href="http://www.freeformportland.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/poster.jpg" target="_blank">poster</a> + <a href="http://www.freeformportland.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/unnamed-3.jpg" target="_blank">USB card</a> (containing special thank you mix, digital artwork, and three 1136 x 640 pixel mobile device wallpapers) for a $50+ donation</li>\r\n	<li><a href="http://www.freeformportland.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/weekend-family-music-hour-ad.png" target="_blank">Kid sing along of Buffy Vampire the Slayer "Once More, With Feeling" musical verbatim</a> from Weekend Family Music Hour for $25+ donation, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Special edition edition <a href="http://www.freeformportland.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/unnamed.jpg" target="_blank">t-shirt with design</a> by one of Studio Visit''s past guests, artist Chandra Glaeseman; printed with the words "Studio Visit," as well as "KFFP" for $25+ donation, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Freeform Portland can koozie in a limited edition <a href="http://www.freeformportland.org/wp-content/uploads/2016/10/KFFP-raincloud-logo-e1475345626535.png">KFFP raincloud design</a> + special thank-you mix by DJ Slay Me of Black Castle for $25+ donation, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>A drawing by The Queen of Siam (The Upstairs Room) for $25+ donation, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Limited Edition Deep Lez Power KFFP frosted etched pint glass for $25+ donation, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Limited edition handmade and hand-screenprinted The Guitar and Other Machines record bag for $25+ donation, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Gift tin featuring one-of-a-kind, handmade spider papercutting by DJ Mrrranda of Spider in the Ear, filled with random trinkets and ephemera, for $60+ donation</li>\r\n	<li>Special thank you mix by DJ Mrrranda of Spider in the Ear, featuring a unique collage as cover art, for $25+ donation, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Limited edition shirt from Teen &amp; Quoz of Terminal Beach for $25+ donation, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Piece of artwork by DJ Zach of Zach''s Radio Show for $25+ donation, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Surprise handmade package with music, ephemera, and an original collage from DJs Gilliflower &amp; Eeronomicon of Turtles Have Short Legs for $25+ donation, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Artwork by DJ RK Heist from Sounds Obscure for $25+ donation, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Copy of a ransom letter, photos of Rusty Nail in captivity, and special thank you mix by Dusty Dale for $25+ donation, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Special thank you batch of CDs from Bloodshot Records in Chicago brought to you by DJ HRPunknStuf for $30+ donation, or $15+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>DJ Zaph Mann''s grab bag of rare CDs for $40+ donation, or $20+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Special merch pack from NONNA of Well Worn and New Territory for a $50+ donation</li>\r\n	<li>Special thank you mixtape + handmade art by DJs Olives and Dan from File Under Various for $25+ donation, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Special thank you mix of songs about money by DJ Eroc of Universal Sound for $25+ donation, or $10+ per month</li>\r\n	<li>Two tickets to Lose Yr Mind Fest (Saturday only) October 8th + One Limited Edition Screen-Printed Lose Yr Mind Fest Poster from Zigzag Body Talk for $40+ donation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<form style="margin-bottom: 1em;" action="https://www.paypal.com/cgi-bin/webscr" method="post" target="_top"><input name="cmd" type="hidden" value="_s-xclick" /><input name="hosted_button_id" type="hidden" value="EXDPWNQFGWYEL" /><input alt="Donate to KFFP" name="submit" src="https://www.paypalobjects.com/en_US/i/btn/btn_donate_LG.gif" type="image" />\r\n\r\nIf you prefer to send a check, please make it out to “Freeform Portland” and mail to:\r\n\r\nFreeform Portland\r\nc/o Donations\r\n5511 N. Albina Ave.\r\nPortland OR 97217\r\n\r\nThank you!\r\n\r\n</form>', 'Donor Drive', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'drive', '', '', '2016-10-07 01:34:31', '2016-10-07 01:34:31', '', 0, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/?page_id=772', 0, 'page', '', 0),
