(931, 3, '2016-10-09 21:59:49', '2016-10-09 21:59:49', '"She''s Lost Control" invades the dark cracks and crevices of post-punk from past to present, from local waves to overseas. We will seep ourselves into goth-laden synths, stomp a lead foot on the pedal board of experimental noise (with the occasional horn of avant-garde jazz), and unveil the raving floors of dance metal. ', 'She''s Lost Control', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'shes-lost-control', '', '', '2016-10-19 04:29:53', '2016-10-19 04:29:53', '', 0, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/?post_type=show&#038;p=931', 0, 'show', '', 0),
(932, 3, '2016-10-09 22:01:55', '2016-10-09 22:01:55', 'Joshua Justice pulls from a cosmically bestowed record collection to bring you Static + Distance. Featuring hot tracks and savory licks from all eras, genres and dimensions with zero regard to the constructs of time, space or laws of physics. Expect heartbreakers, burners, shakers, bummers and more. Always solid jams.', 'Static + Distance', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'static-distance', '', '', '2016-10-09 22:01:55', '2016-10-09 22:01:55', '', 0, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/?post_type=show&#038;p=932', 0, 'show', '', 0),
(933, 3, '2016-10-09 22:04:17', '2016-10-09 22:04:17', 'Playing primarily physical media. Records and tapes.  Music is cheaper than therapy. Psych, Surf, Modern and old.  Music from across the globe will be played, as well as local favorites being highlighted.  All shapes and sizes of music will be included.  This hour will make the bummer summer slightly more bearable.  Focus is primarily on the jamz, with guest musicians coming in for interviews, discussions, playlists.', 'Bummer Summer', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'bummer-summer', '', '', '2017-03-31 20:20:30', '2017-04-01 03:20:30', '', 0, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/?post_type=show&#038;p=933', 0, 'show', '', 0),
(934, 3, '2016-10-09 22:06:07', '2016-10-09 22:06:07', '“Under the Radar/On the Rise” aims to shine a light on a portion of music making a stir on the interwebs where mainstream radio stays mum. Highlighting newer music from a variety of indie formats including rock/folk/soul and R&amp;B, remix and dance; UTR/OTR is frequently thematic.', 'Under the Radar/On the Rise', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'under-the-radar-on-the-rise', '', '', '2017-03-27 19:42:41', '2017-03-28 02:42:41', '', 0, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/?post_type=show&#038;p=934', 0, 'show', '', 0),
(936, 3, '2016-10-09 22:27:35', '2016-10-09 22:27:35', 'It is the year 1453 A.E (after earth). A cosmic wind carries the distant pulsing wave of a long forgotten radio transmission. This waning emission of noise collides with a golden meteor headed for the surface of an unknown planet. The collision with the crust of this planet is one of such force that the meteor is flattened into a circular plate. Two escha-hominids stumble upon this galactic trash while hiking through a clouded forest. The golden disc is later placed on their alien music adapter. Music, discussion, art, purity, beauty in its most celestial form plays from their unworthy speakers. What they are listening to is this week''s episode of Hermetically Sealed.\r\n\r\nHermetically Sealed is a weekly exploration of the cosmos through the vessel of music and half-baked musings. This show presents an invocation to the universe in the form of a radio broadcast. All songs chosen are inspired by current astrological transits. All discussion is rooted in the subject of metaphysical quandary and innovation. All listeners are encouraged to adapt with the energy of the broadcast towards a weirder tomorrow.', 'Hermetically Sealed', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'hermetically-sealed', '', '', '2017-03-31 21:03:09', '2017-04-01 04:03:09', '', 0, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/?post_type=show&#038;p=936', 0, 'show', '', 0),
