(1226, 128, '2017-03-27 17:39:24', '2017-03-28 00:39:24', 'Dear Future, is a weekly series of audioletters from normal people trapped in this temporal moment to the entire distant future human population. Real people write and speak to The Future like an individual, like an intimate, long-distance pen pal in whom they can confide their troubles and ambitions. Narrators can speculate as to how The Future''s daily life might differ from their own based on technological advances, social progress, political climate, and environmental destruction, to name a few examples. Each episode will feature 3 to 4 letters on a flexible theme like parenthood, public school, or hygiene with requisite ventures into personal, emotional, narrative. Audio will be nonfiction mixed together with music and commentary from me, Shea, tying it all together.\r\n\r\nThis idea comes from the question of whether life in "the good old days" really used to be all that different from life as we know it now. Nostalgia for simpler times, or even just the supposed simplicity of youth, compels us to lament the passage of time as a force of inherent loss. These episodes will grapple with this question while serving as time capsules for theoretical future generations who will probably still be dealing with the same pesky nostalgia.', 'Dear Future,', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'dear-future', '', '', '2017-03-31 20:39:30', '2017-04-01 03:39:30', '', 0, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/?post_type=show&#038;p=1226', 0, 'show', '', 0),
