(1271, 128, '2017-03-27 20:51:46', '2017-03-28 03:51:46', 'It is the year 1453 A.E (after earth). A cosmic wind carries the distant pulsing wave of a long forgotten radio transmission. This waning emission of noise collides with a golden meteor headed for the surface of an unknown planet. The collision with the crust of this planet is one of such force that the meteor is flattened into a circular plate. Two escha-hominids stumble upon this galactic trash while hiking through a clouded forest. The golden disc is later placed on their alien music adapter. Music, discussion, art, purity, beauty in its most celestial form plays from their unworthy speakers. What they are listening to is this week''s episode of Hermetically Sealed.\n\nHermetically Sealed is a weekly exploration of the cosmos through the vessel of music and half-baked musings. This show presents an invocation to the universe in the form of a radio broadcast. All songs chosen are inspired by current astrological transits. All discussion is rooted in the subject of metaphysical quandary and innovation. All listeners are encouraged to adapt with the energy of the broadcast towards a weirder tomorrow.', 'Hermetically Sealed', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '936-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-03-27 20:51:46', '2017-03-28 03:51:46', '', 936, 'http://www.freeformportland.org/blog/936-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
